After not being able to reopen on June 8 due to two of its teachers testing positive for Covid-19, the statement now assures both learners and parents that the school, with the departments of education and health, has taken every measure to ensure a safe learning environment. ALSO READ: Two Lowveld High teachers test positive for Covid-19 JR Nkosi, HOD of the Department of Education, has declared that the school is ready for the return of grade 12s on Monday. The hostel will open on Sunday. Gates will open at 07:00 (half an hour earlier than usual) to receive learners so as to allow more time for the screening process. All learners will receive two cloth masks, issued to the school by the Department of Education.   